=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Decay_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 301 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, energy distribution is late, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: moderate
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: late

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 301.3973
  harmonic_decay_rate: -10.0025
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5829
  pitch_clarity: 270.2839
  inharmonicity: 0.0082
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -14.3102
  resonance_freq: 301.4648

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Decay Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Decay.html
// Tags: Decay, Classes, envelope
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
// Used as an evelope generator
(
play({
    Decay.ar(
        in: Impulse.ar(XLine.kr(5,50,10), 0.25),
        decayTime: 0.2,
        mul: FSinOsc.ar(300)
    )
})
)
